16
00:00:12,305 --> 00:00:12,421
http://hiqve.com

17
00:00:12,422 --> 00:00:12,539
http://hiqve.com/

18
00:00:12,540 --> 00:00:15,540
http://hiqve.com/

19
00:00:17,564 --> 00:00:19,524
<i>A long awaited truth!</i>

20
00:00:19,608 --> 00:00:22,611
<i>A distress signal has been received
at the Jedi Temple</i>

21
00:00:22,694 --> 00:00:26,489
<i>and Master Plo Koon has been
dispatched to investigate its origin.</i>

22
00:00:26,573 --> 00:00:28,700
<i>The signal is from a ship
thought to be lost</i>

23
00:00:28,783 --> 00:00:31,536
<i>and was last known to be
in the possession of a Jedi Master</i>

24
00:00:31,620 --> 00:00:33,496
<i>who was killed long ago.</i>

25
00:00:37,334 --> 00:00:39,836
Can anyone hear us? Come in please.

26
00:00:40,128 --> 00:00:42,047
We're not getting anything over here.

27
00:00:42,130 --> 00:00:44,716
We're off. We must be way off.

28
00:00:44,799 --> 00:00:47,052
<i>Negative. It is here.</i>

29
00:00:47,135 --> 00:00:50,222
<i>The data specifically states.
It has got to be.</i>

30
00:00:50,347 --> 00:00:52,515
We've scanned the area three times.

31
00:00:52,599 --> 00:00:55,185
This is a wasteland. There's nothing.

32
00:00:57,812 --> 00:01:00,941
All of our information
pinpoints it is here.

33
00:01:01,024 --> 00:01:02,651
<i>I don't know what to tell you, sir.</i>

34
00:01:02,734 --> 00:01:06,238
<i>We're getting no visual,
and no recognition on the scanner.</i>

35
00:01:06,321 --> 00:01:10,158
We must locate the source of the signal,
Commander, press on!

36
00:01:10,492 --> 00:01:13,119
Wait, I think I've found something.

37
00:01:13,203 --> 00:01:15,705
It's very faint, sir.

38
00:01:16,248 --> 00:01:17,374
That is it.

39
00:01:20,669 --> 00:01:24,256
Halt! Halt! Halt all vehicles!

40
00:01:53,034 --> 00:01:56,371
The hull shows substantial
scoring and wear.

41
00:01:56,454 --> 00:01:59,666
Whenever it crashed, it wasn't recently.

42
00:02:00,542 --> 00:02:04,671
General Plo, the scans check out,
it's a T-6 Shuttle all right,

43
00:02:04,754 --> 00:02:07,507
serial number 7-7-5-5-1 -9.

44
00:02:18,852 --> 00:02:21,062
I want the entire area cleared.

45
00:02:21,229 --> 00:02:23,815
We're taking everything
back to Coruscant.

46
00:02:23,898 --> 00:02:26,234
-Everything?
-Everything!

47
00:02:39,164 --> 00:02:42,250
Then it is the lost ship
of Master Sifo-Dyas?

48
00:02:42,375 --> 00:02:45,337
<i>I found this at the crash site.</i>

49
00:02:47,088 --> 00:02:51,092
The lightsaber of Sifo-Dyas it is.
Never found when he died it was.

50
00:02:53,053 --> 00:02:55,805
Master Kenobi, remind the Council
of what you discovered

51
00:02:55,889 --> 00:02:59,184
regarding Master Sifo-Dyas before
the start of the Clone War.

52
00:02:59,309 --> 00:03:03,938
My investigation of the bounty hunter
Jango Fett led to Kamino.

53
00:03:04,105 --> 00:03:06,983
The Kaminoans recounted
that it was Jedi Master Sifo-Dyas

54
00:03:07,067 --> 00:03:09,444
who ordered the production
of a Clone Army.

55
00:03:09,611 --> 00:03:13,615
Without the consent of the Council
or the Senate he did this.

56
00:03:13,698 --> 00:03:15,492
Prior to the blockade of Naboo,

57
00:03:15,575 --> 00:03:21,414
Sifo-Dyas sat on this Council until
we judged his ideas to be too extreme.

58
00:03:21,706 --> 00:03:22,707
<i>Indeed.</i>

59
00:03:22,791 --> 00:03:25,377
<i>He said he foresaw a great conflict,</i>

60
00:03:25,460 --> 00:03:28,463
<i>and that the Republic would need
to raise an army.</i>

61
00:03:28,546 --> 00:03:31,132
<i>At the time the Council
rejected those ideas.</i>

62
00:03:31,800 --> 00:03:34,886
Well, it's not the first time
we've been wrong recently, is it?

63
00:03:34,969 --> 00:03:39,808
The creation of the Clone Army,
kept secret from us Sifo-Dyas did.

64
00:03:39,933 --> 00:03:42,811
How this was done we know not.

65
00:03:42,894 --> 00:03:45,897
Yet now, a new piece
of the puzzle we have,

66
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:49,609
perhaps clarity, it will bring us, yes.

67
00:03:53,363 --> 00:03:59,327
Our records definitively state
that Master Sifo-Dyas died on Felucia.

68
00:03:59,828 --> 00:04:04,958
In the fifth quarter, a small skirmish
broke out between the native Felucians.

69
00:04:05,333 --> 00:04:07,085
Master Sifo-Dyas was assigned

70
00:04:07,168 --> 00:04:10,505
to negotiate peace talks
between the tribes.

71
00:04:11,005 --> 00:04:15,468
The negotiations failed
and Sifo-Dyas was killed.

72
00:04:15,927 --> 00:04:17,929
<i>What became of his body?</i>

73
00:04:18,012 --> 00:04:20,640
I am afraid I cannot answer that.

74
00:04:20,723 --> 00:04:25,353
Any further information on this incident
has been sealed.

75
00:04:25,437 --> 00:04:27,147
On whose authority?

76
00:04:27,230 --> 00:04:29,983
By the office
of the Supreme Chancellor.

77
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:32,444
Thank you, Madame Jocasta.

78
00:04:35,738 --> 00:04:39,075
To Felucia
Skywalker and Kenobi will go.

79
00:04:39,159 --> 00:04:44,581
A trail long cold it is, yet still
lay hidden there a clue might be.

80
00:04:44,664 --> 00:04:48,626
Question all who were present the day
of Sifo-Dyas's death, you must.

81
00:04:48,710 --> 00:04:50,670
And what of the sealed file?

82
00:04:50,753 --> 00:04:53,131
Speak with the Chancellor
personally I will,

83
00:04:53,214 --> 00:04:56,468
to see what part in this the politics
of the Senate have played.

84
00:05:03,850 --> 00:05:06,978
Master Sifo-Dyas?

85
00:05:07,061 --> 00:05:10,773
Forgive me, I'm afraid I am not familiar
with that name.

86
00:05:10,899 --> 00:05:14,068
Died some time ago he did on Felucia.

87
00:05:14,152 --> 00:05:16,112
Investigating his death we are,

88
00:05:16,196 --> 00:05:20,200
and yet sealed by the Chancellor's
office some of his files were.

89
00:05:20,283 --> 00:05:23,828
And what is the nature
of your investigation?

90
00:05:23,912 --> 00:05:28,333
A Jedi matter it is, Chancellor.
Add to your troubles I would not.

91
00:05:28,416 --> 00:05:34,130
That is very considerate, Master Yoda.
May I at least ask when Master...

92
00:05:34,756 --> 00:05:36,382
Sifo-Dyas.

93
00:05:36,466 --> 00:05:42,388
Yes, Master Sifo-Dyas,
may I ask when he was killed?

94
00:05:42,472 --> 00:05:44,849
Over 10 years ago it was.

95
00:05:44,933 --> 00:05:49,854
Well, that explains it.
I'm afraid this was before my time.

96
00:05:49,938 --> 00:05:54,734
Ten years ago, I was a humble Senator
serving the planet Naboo.

97
00:05:55,527 --> 00:05:58,029
Only my predecessor,
Chancellor Valorum,

98
00:05:58,112 --> 00:06:00,657
would have the answers you seek.

99
00:06:00,740 --> 00:06:03,117
I suggest you speak with him.

100
00:06:03,451 --> 00:06:06,204
Very well. Thank you, Chancellor.

101
00:06:15,421 --> 00:06:17,423
<i>I have spoken with
the tribal leaders on Felucia.</i>

102
00:06:17,549 --> 00:06:21,094
<i>They use a very ancient dialect
which is hard to understand</i>

103
00:06:21,177 --> 00:06:22,428
<i>but from what I can make out,</i>

104
00:06:22,512 --> 00:06:25,974
<i>when Master Sifo-Dyas died,
he was not alone.</i>

105
00:06:26,057 --> 00:06:28,059
<i>There was a second Jedi
here with him.</i>

106
00:06:28,142 --> 00:06:30,436
And the name of this second Jedi?

107
00:06:30,520 --> 00:06:34,607
<i>Either I don't understand them
or they won't say. It's hard to tell.</i>

108
00:06:34,691 --> 00:06:37,068
<i>This is a primitive people
we are dealing with.</i>

109
00:06:37,151 --> 00:06:39,821
<i>After his death,
they cremated Sifo-Dyas's body</i>

110
00:06:39,904 --> 00:06:42,740
<i>and I'm afraid the trail goes cold there.</i>

111
00:06:42,824 --> 00:06:44,826
<i>Did you have any success
with the Chancellor?</i>

112
00:06:45,910 --> 00:06:48,663
As much success as usual, I am afraid.

113
00:06:48,746 --> 00:06:53,167
Pointed in another direction I am now,
to speak with Valorum I go.

114
00:07:06,222 --> 00:07:09,767
It's been a long time, my friend.
What can I do for you?

115
00:07:10,184 --> 00:07:14,772
A file sealed by your administration
the Jedi Council has come across.

116
00:07:14,856 --> 00:07:16,899
The subject of the file?

117
00:07:17,442 --> 00:07:19,611
Jedi Master Sifo-Dyas.

118
00:07:19,694 --> 00:07:20,695
Sifo-Dyas?

119
00:07:21,904 --> 00:07:23,406
When I was Chancellor,

120
00:07:23,489 --> 00:07:27,744
I sent him on a mission to deal
with a flare up in the Pyke syndicate.

121
00:07:28,369 --> 00:07:29,412
The Pykes?

122
00:07:29,495 --> 00:07:32,540
A powerful part of the spice cartel.

123
00:07:32,624 --> 00:07:34,792
Their criminal activities
had allowed them

124
00:07:34,876 --> 00:07:38,713
to almost completely control
the production of raw spice

125
00:07:38,838 --> 00:07:40,882
used to create a powerful drug.

126
00:07:41,007 --> 00:07:46,054
We were facing a full scale war
underneath the surface of Coruscant.

127
00:07:46,179 --> 00:07:48,473
Knowing of his expertise
on the Underworld,

128
00:07:48,556 --> 00:07:52,852
I contacted Master Sifo-Dyas
to stabilize the problem.

129
00:07:53,311 --> 00:07:56,397
Know of this, the Jedi Council did not.

130
00:07:56,522 --> 00:07:59,651
The Senate Committee
assigned to the matter

131
00:07:59,734 --> 00:08:04,155
feared that open discussions
with such a criminal element

132
00:08:04,238 --> 00:08:06,324
could legitimize their activities

133
00:08:06,407 --> 00:08:09,994
and give strength to opposition leaders
within the bureaucracy.

134
00:08:10,078 --> 00:08:13,373
Secrecy was our only choice.

135
00:08:13,456 --> 00:08:17,502
The timing of these negotiations,
when were they to take place?

136
00:08:17,585 --> 00:08:22,674
I cannot remember the precise timing,
I'm afraid. It was so long ago.

137
00:08:22,757 --> 00:08:26,386
I do remember that
the talks were postponed

138
00:08:26,469 --> 00:08:30,306
not long after our delegates
arrived on Oba Diah.

139
00:08:30,390 --> 00:08:33,601
Something about a flare up
of activity on Felucia.

140
00:08:33,768 --> 00:08:37,939
Yes, intervene on Felucia,
the Council insisted Sifo-Dyas did,

141
00:08:38,064 --> 00:08:42,735
but tell me, Chancellor, who was
the other Jedi you sent with Sifo-Dyas?

142
00:08:42,860 --> 00:08:46,531
Other Jedi? I know of no other Jedi.

143
00:08:46,614 --> 00:08:50,785
There was only my personal aide,
Silman, and Sifo-Dyas.

144
00:08:51,244 --> 00:08:54,247
I'm afraid they were
both killed on Felucia.

145
00:08:54,872 --> 00:08:57,709
Personal aid? Silman?

146
00:09:01,504 --> 00:09:06,759
<i>Tell me, why do the Jedi
look for Sifo-Dyas?</i>

147
00:09:06,843 --> 00:09:09,679
<i>What trail are they following?</i>

148
00:09:09,762 --> 00:09:13,599
If there is a trail, it is unknown to me.

149
00:09:14,142 --> 00:09:19,814
<i>Retrace your steps,
find this loose end, and eliminate it.</i>

150
00:09:20,314 --> 00:09:23,359
I understand what is at stake, my Lord.

151
00:09:23,443 --> 00:09:26,487
I will go to the Pykes and take care of it.

152
00:09:26,571 --> 00:09:32,660
<i>This is not the first time you have
proven to be clumsy, Lord Tyranus.</i>

153
00:09:32,785 --> 00:09:37,165
<i>You know the price of failure.</i>

154
00:09:45,465 --> 00:09:48,050
<i>The Felucians know
nothing of this Silman.</i>

155
00:09:48,134 --> 00:09:50,928
<i>No one there seems
to know anything about him.</i>

156
00:09:51,012 --> 00:09:52,889
<i>What's that symbol he's wearing?</i>

157
00:09:52,972 --> 00:09:57,059
The symbol of the high Chancellor
before the war, Chancellor Valorum.

158
00:09:58,686 --> 00:10:01,773
<i>So, we have one dead Jedi with
no physical evidence of a body,</i>

159
00:10:01,856 --> 00:10:05,318
<i>a second Jedi who appeared
on Felucia that we have no record of,</i>

160
00:10:05,401 --> 00:10:09,906
<i>and now this Silman, personal attaché
to the Chancellor, is missing?</i>

161
00:10:10,531 --> 00:10:14,076
<i>Yet, now we know Sifo-Dyas
and Silman were both on Oba Diah,</i>

162
00:10:14,160 --> 00:10:15,745
<i>according to Chancellor Valorum.</i>

163
00:10:16,662 --> 00:10:21,459
The crashed shuttle I found was located
on a moon which orbits the Pyke planet.

164
00:10:21,542 --> 00:10:25,713
To the Pykes you must go,
to Oba Diah, yes.

165
00:11:38,286 --> 00:11:43,916
I cannot remember the last time
a Jedi came here.

166
00:11:44,000 --> 00:11:46,794
Many years it has been.

167
00:11:46,878 --> 00:11:48,796
Funny you should say that.

168
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:53,217
We're looking for a Jedi that got
lost here. His name is Sifo-Dyas.

169
00:11:54,385 --> 00:11:58,472
The Jedi Sifo-Dyas was here,

170
00:11:58,556 --> 00:12:03,144
but that was a long time ago.

171
00:12:03,269 --> 00:12:07,899
Master Sifo-Dyas's ship was found
crashed on a moon orbiting this world.

172
00:12:08,107 --> 00:12:12,987
What you found, we know nothing of.

173
00:12:13,654 --> 00:12:18,034
Would the Jedi like
to join us for a refreshment?

174
00:12:19,243 --> 00:12:21,871
The Pykes offer is kindly accepted.

175
00:12:29,170 --> 00:12:30,796
To friendship.

176
00:12:33,257 --> 00:12:35,927
-Friendship.
-Friendship.

177
00:12:39,680 --> 00:12:42,224
What an interesting necklace that is.

178
00:12:42,308 --> 00:12:43,434
May I have a look?

179
00:12:45,519 --> 00:12:50,191
Perhaps the Pykes have taken
enough of the Jedi's time.

180
00:12:50,274 --> 00:12:51,943
No, no. It's no bother at all,

181
00:12:52,026 --> 00:12:55,237
the Jedi are happy
to know all the Pykes' secrets.

182
00:12:57,782 --> 00:13:00,993
We have no quarrel with the Jedi.

183
00:13:01,077 --> 00:13:02,954
Maybe you should tell us
why you're wearing

184
00:13:03,037 --> 00:13:05,581
the crest of the Chancellor's
personal advisor?

185
00:13:07,291 --> 00:13:09,168
I am confused.

186
00:13:09,251 --> 00:13:14,048
Is the Jedi looking for a Jedi Master
or someone else?

187
00:13:14,215 --> 00:13:18,177
Stop playing games.
Sifo-Dyas was traveling with an advisor.

188
00:13:18,260 --> 00:13:20,846
They were sent here
to negotiate with you.

189
00:13:23,432 --> 00:13:28,229
Well, it looks like you have finally put
the pieces together.

190
00:13:28,312 --> 00:13:31,899
The man you are looking for is here.

191
00:13:42,493 --> 00:13:48,541
The Pykes wanted to gain an advantage
over the other crime families,

192
00:13:48,666 --> 00:13:50,543
so alliances were made.

193
00:13:50,626 --> 00:13:54,130
One alliance was with
a man named Tyranus.

194
00:13:54,213 --> 00:13:55,881
I've heard that name before,

195
00:13:55,965 --> 00:13:59,260
Jango Fett mentioned it during
my Kamino investigation.

196
00:13:59,343 --> 00:14:02,847
Tyranus wanted Sifo-Dyas dead,

197
00:14:02,930 --> 00:14:07,101
the Pykes were well paid
to shoot down his ship.

198
00:14:07,893 --> 00:14:13,983
However, any man that is willing to pay
to have a Jedi killed is dangerous,

199
00:14:14,066 --> 00:14:15,735
and unpredictable.

200
00:14:15,818 --> 00:14:22,199
The Pykes inspected the crash,
to retrieve the Jedi's body for proof.

201
00:14:22,283 --> 00:14:29,165
But, with the dead Jedi,
the Pykes found another, still alive.

202
00:14:29,248 --> 00:14:31,542
Silman, the Chancellor's aide?

203
00:14:31,625 --> 00:14:35,087
The Pykes gave Tyranus Sifo-Dyas,

204
00:14:35,171 --> 00:14:39,050
but the Pykes did not
tell Tyranus of Silman.

205
00:14:39,133 --> 00:14:43,262
The Pykes needed insurance.

206
00:14:43,345 --> 00:14:44,805
Insurance?

207
00:14:44,889 --> 00:14:50,102
Yes, and now the Pykes can bargain.

208
00:14:50,311 --> 00:14:56,692
We give you Silman, you forget about
the Pykes' treachery against the Jedi.

209
00:15:12,875 --> 00:15:14,418
Hello?

210
00:15:15,419 --> 00:15:19,006
-Who's there?
-We are Jedi sent to find you.

211
00:15:19,507 --> 00:15:20,591
Jedi?

212
00:15:22,218 --> 00:15:23,761
To find me?

213
00:15:23,844 --> 00:15:25,262
Why me?

214
00:15:25,346 --> 00:15:29,892
I was betrayed, forgotten. Long ago.

215
00:15:30,476 --> 00:15:32,561
No one knew you were alive.

216
00:15:32,645 --> 00:15:35,314
Quick. Maybe you have some food.

217
00:15:35,397 --> 00:15:37,858
Have you any food?

218
00:15:38,734 --> 00:15:40,194
Of course.

219
00:15:43,864 --> 00:15:46,575
Thank you, my friend. A supply bar!

220
00:15:47,535 --> 00:15:49,245
Delicious.

221
00:15:49,328 --> 00:15:53,457
You see, I was so frightened
I would have nothing to serve.

222
00:15:55,918 --> 00:15:57,086
Serve?

223
00:15:57,461 --> 00:16:01,799
My babies, they get so angry
when I have nothing to serve.

224
00:16:01,882 --> 00:16:04,885
We might have a problem here.

225
00:16:21,443 --> 00:16:24,405
Tyranus, you are no longer
welcome here.

226
00:16:28,409 --> 00:16:31,245
I think you've been cooped up
in here too long, old man.

227
00:16:31,328 --> 00:16:33,455
We've come to take you home.

228
00:16:33,539 --> 00:16:39,378
Home? No, no, this is my home!
I can't leave my friends.

229
00:16:39,503 --> 00:16:42,214
You were traveling with
Jedi Master Sifo-Dyas.

230
00:16:42,298 --> 00:16:44,091
Tell us what happed to him.

231
00:16:46,594 --> 00:16:48,095
Sifo-Dyas?

232
00:16:48,179 --> 00:16:49,305
He died.

233
00:16:49,388 --> 00:16:51,348
Died. Died. Died. Died.

234
00:16:51,432 --> 00:16:52,725
Tricked we were.

235
00:16:54,185 --> 00:16:58,314
The Pykes are not to be trusted.
No. No, no, no. Oh, no, no, no.

236
00:16:58,480 --> 00:17:04,445
But the Pykes were not the ones.
No, no, the Pykes were not the reason.

237
00:17:08,282 --> 00:17:09,909
Who was responsible?

238
00:17:12,786 --> 00:17:15,539
Someone powerful...

239
00:17:15,623 --> 00:17:20,294
Someone who wanted to be Sifo-Dyas!

240
00:17:33,557 --> 00:17:34,558
Why?

241
00:17:34,642 --> 00:17:36,268
All is deception.

242
00:17:37,686 --> 00:17:41,482
Can't you see... Because... Because...

243
00:17:55,996 --> 00:17:59,959
Dooku ! For once you actually came
to do your own dirty work.

244
00:18:01,210 --> 00:18:05,339
Sometimes things
are just that important.

245
00:18:55,639 --> 00:18:59,852
You have no business
left with the Pykes, Tyranus.

246
00:18:59,977 --> 00:19:03,022
Tyranus?
You are the man called Tyranus?

247
00:19:03,105 --> 00:19:05,524
I told you everything
you needed to know

248
00:19:05,607 --> 00:19:09,820
on Geonosis
all those years ago, Kenobi.

249
00:19:09,903 --> 00:19:13,490
You should have joined me.
Sifo-Dyas understood.

250
00:19:13,574 --> 00:19:17,411
He saw the future,
that is why he helped me.

251
00:19:17,494 --> 00:19:19,246
You lie!

252
00:19:19,330 --> 00:19:22,916
Minister Lom, if you are going
to help us, now is the time.

253
00:19:23,083 --> 00:19:25,210
Kill Tyranus!

254
00:20:03,582 --> 00:20:05,334
I'll give you a push!

255
00:20:44,331 --> 00:20:45,624
Know now we do,

256
00:20:45,707 --> 00:20:49,878
that guide the creation of the clones
from the beginning, Dooku did.

257
00:20:51,463 --> 00:20:54,341
Our enemy created an army for us.

258
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:58,470
If this was known,
public confidence in the war effort,

259
00:20:58,554 --> 00:21:01,098
the Jedi and the Republic would vanish.

260
00:21:01,181 --> 00:21:02,850
There would be mass chaos.

261
00:21:03,392 --> 00:21:06,228
Cover up this discovery we must.

262
00:21:06,770 --> 00:21:09,857
No one,
not even the Chancellor may know.

263
00:21:11,775 --> 00:21:14,486
Valiant men,
the clones have proven to be,

264
00:21:14,570 --> 00:21:17,781
saved my life and yours
they have many times.

265
00:21:17,865 --> 00:21:22,828
Believe in them we must,
win the war swiftly we must,

266
00:21:23,912 --> 00:21:26,999
before our enemy's designs
reach completion,

267
00:21:27,082 --> 00:21:28,917
whatever they may be.

268
00:21:29,543 --> 00:21:32,713
Are you sure
we are taking the right path?

269
00:21:34,214 --> 00:21:36,300
The right path, no.

270
00:21:37,009 --> 00:21:39,720
The only path, yes.

271
00:21:41,555 --> 00:21:46,143
Designed by the Dark Lord of the Sith,
this web is.

272
00:21:46,810 --> 00:21:49,938
For now, play his game we must.

273
00:21:49,962 --> 00:21:54,962
http://hiqve.com/

